- The fund has been able to provide immediate support to expand health service for the COVID crisis as well as other protection measures to women and vulnerable population. For the support for the health service, National & Provincial Health Emergency Operations Centers facilitated to constitute Emergency Medical Deployment Teams (EMDT) with personnel sourced from the Hub hospitals network; 
- Support to quarantine sites, isolation centres and holding centres with NFIs namely cloth masks, sanitizers and mosquito nets.  More than 5000 individuals including returnee migrants in the 11 isolation centres, 3 holding centres and 19 quarantine sites have been reached in the four districts- Morang, Illam, Sunsari and Jhapa spread across 14 local levels, sharing borders with the neighboring country India in Province One. 
- For other protection measures, Recruited the GBV Sub Cluster Information Manager (UNV) to provide support/technical assistance to an expanded rural electrification programme.

